caption.center: Lloyd DOTSON-BEY, Appellant, v. STATE of Missouri, Respondent.

court.center: Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District.

opinion.posture: Appeal from the Circuit Court of Dekalb County, Missouri, Warren L. McElwain, Judge.Page 892
opinion.attorneys:
Susan L. Hogan, Appellate Defender, Kansas City, MO, attorney for appellant.
Jeremiah W. (Jay) Nixon, Attorney General, Karen L. Kramer, Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, attorneys for respondent.
opinion.panel: Before HOWARD, C.J., and BRECKENRIDGE and NEWTON, JJ.
opinion.opinion_text:
Order PER CURIAM.
Lloyd Dotson-Bey appeals the denial of his Rule 29.15 motion for post-conviction relief. The motion court's findings and conclusions that Dotson-Bey's appellate counsel was not ineffective are not clearly erroneous. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum has been provided to the parties.
The motion court's judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
